<div class="calcpad-output">
 <!-- Evaluates $\int_{-1}^{1}\sqrt{1-x^2}\, dx$ with three quadrature rules — Boole (Newton-Cotes), Gauss-Legendre and tanh-sinh — at five nodes.
<p>Tabulates the relative error of each scheme against the analytical result $\pi/2$. -->
 <p>
  Function -
  <span class="eq">
   <var>f</var>
   (
   <var>x</var>
   )  =
   <span class="o0">
    <span class="r">√</span>
    1 −
    <var>x</var>
    <sup>2</sup>
   </span>
  </span>
 </p>
 <p>
  Theoretical value of the integral -
  <span class="eq">
   <var>I</var>
   =
   <span class="dvc">
    <var>π</var>
    <span class="dvl">
    </span>
    2
   </span>
   =
   <span class="dvc">
    3.14
    <span class="dvl">
    </span>
    2
   </span>
   = 1.57
  </span>
 </p>
 <p>
  Number of nodes -
  <span class="eq">
   <var>n</var>
   = 5
  </span>
 </p>
 <h4>Boole′s rule (Newton-Cotes for n = 4)</h4>
 <hr/>
 <p>
  Step -
  <span class="eq">
   <var>h</var>
   = 0.5
  </span>
 </p>
 <p>
